1. Authentication — Unified Smart Login System
How It Works
There is one login page for both admins and drivers. After credentials are verified, the backend returns a role field (super_admin | admin | driver), and the frontend automatically redirects:

super_admin / admin → Admin Dashboard
driver → Driver Dashboard

Admin Registration (Company Onboarding)
New companies register through a "Register New Company" form:
Fields:

Full Name
Company Name
Email Address
Password + Confirm Password
Role Assignment: Super Admin | Admin

No self-serve driver sign-up. Drivers are only registered by an admin from inside the dashboard.
Driver Registration (Admin-Side Only)
Admins register drivers from the Ambulance Management page. Driver accounts are created with:

Full Name
Phone Number
Email Address (used as login)
Auto-generated or admin-set Password
Assigned Ambulance
Driver Photo (optional)

Login Page (Shared — Admin & Driver)
Fields:

Email Address
Password
Remember Me checkbox → persistent session (30 days via httpOnly cookie or localStorage JWT with extended expiry)

Additional Features:

Forgot Password / Reset Password link
Session timeout with auto-logout after inactivity
Role detection on successful login → smart redirect

Auth Architecture

JWT authentication (short-lived access tokens + long-lived refresh tokens)
Role-based access control (RBAC): super_admin, admin, driver
Refresh token rotation for persistent sessions
Secure httpOnly cookies for Remember Me token storage
Protected routes per role on the frontend


