5. Real-Time Synchronization Architecture
All three surfaces (Client, Admin, Driver) must stay in sync via real-time channels.
Events to Synchronize
EventSenderReceiversNew booking requestClient AppAdmin Dashboard + assigned DriverDriver accepts bookingDriver AppClient App (tracking activates) + AdminDriver denies bookingDriver AppAdmin Dashboard (reassign)Driver location updateDriver App (GPS)Client App (live marker) + Admin mapPatient location updateClient App (GPS)Driver App (live marker) + Admin mapTrip completedDriver AppClient App (rating page shown) + AdminPayment confirmedAdminClient App (receipt / status)
Tech Stack for Real-Time

Socket.io (primary — room-based per booking ID)
Firebase Realtime Database (optional fallback / location streams)
WebSockets (raw WS where Socket.io is overkill)

Room Strategy
Each booking creates a Socket.io room: room:booking_{bookingId}
Client, Driver, and Admin all join this room for that booking's lifecycle.

6. Dispatch Display — No Generic Labels
Everywhere a dispatch or ambulance assignment is shown (Client tracking page, Admin booking list, Driver screen), the display must show:
🚑 [Company Name] — Driver: [Driver Full Name] (#[Driver ID]) — Unit: [Ambulance Number]
Never display a generic label like "Rescue Unit" or "Driver 1".

7. Backend API Plan
Auth

POST /auth/register — company/admin registration
POST /auth/login — unified login (returns role + tokens)
POST /auth/refresh — refresh access token
POST /auth/logout
POST /auth/forgot-password
POST /auth/reset-password

Ambulances & Drivers

GET /ambulances — list (with filters)
POST /ambulances — register new ambulance
PATCH /ambulances/:id/status — activate/deactivate
POST /drivers — register new driver (admin only)
GET /drivers/:id

Bookings

GET /bookings — list (admin)
POST /bookings — create (client, public)
GET /bookings/:id
PATCH /bookings/:id/assign — assign ambulance
PATCH /bookings/:id/accept — driver accepts
PATCH /bookings/:id/deny — driver denies
PATCH /bookings/:id/dispatch
PATCH /bookings/:id/complete

Location

POST /location/patient — update patient location
POST /location/driver — update driver location
GET /location/ambulances/nearby — public, for client map

Payments

GET /payments
PATCH /payments/:id/confirm

Feedback

POST /feedback — client submits
GET /feedback — admin views

Reports

GET /reports/:type?startDate=&endDate=&... — filtered report data


